gemini-1.5-pro.ocr_text:
GREAT SMOKY MOUNTAINS NATIONAL PARK
GSMNP10728

Plants of Tennessee

Diapensiaceae
*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

Tennessee: Sevier County
35.64389° Latitude -83.48373° Longitude 3760 ft. Elevation
Quadrangle: Mount Le Conte West Prong Little Pigeon Watershed
T. 11S, R. 73E, Sect. 6
The Great Smoky Mountains National Park. Along U.S. Route 441, at site formerly known as
The Buckeye Nature Trail Parking Area. Coordinate Datum: WGS84/NAD83.

Steep little east of south-facing (155°) slope with *Acer rubrum*, *Betula lenta*, *Quercus rubra*
(tree about 4 feet d.b.h.), *Tsuga canadensis* (large, dead tree), *Hamamelis virginiana*, *Ilex
montana*, *Rhododendron maximum*, *Rubus canadensis*, *Dennstaedtia punctilobula*,
*Lysimachia quadrifolia*, etc. Evergreen perennial herb.

42239 Loy R. Phillippe & James R. Payne
6 October 2009

Illinois Natural History Survey (ILLS)


*Galax urceolata*
